### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Project Manager — Auth API Test Suite
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Usage: Install "REST Client" extension in VS Code, then
### click "Send Request" above each request block.
###
### Run tests in order: Register → Login → Protected → Refresh → Logout
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api/v1
@contentType = application/json


### ─── 1. Health Check ─────────────────────────────────────────
GET http://localhost:3000/health


### ─── 2. Register a new organization + admin user ─────────────
# @name registerRequest
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "organizationName": "Acme Corp",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john@acme.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123"
}


### ─── 3. Register — Validation Error (weak password) ──────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "organizationName": "Another Corp",
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "jane@another.com",
  "password": "weak"
}


### ─── 4. Login ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# @name loginRequest
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "john@acme.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123"
}


### ─── 5. Login — Wrong password ───────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "john@acme.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword123"
}


### ─── 6. Access Protected Route ───────────────────────────────
# Copy the accessToken from the login response and paste below
@accessToken = {{loginRequest.response.body.data.accessToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/test-protected
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### ─── 7. Access Admin Route ───────────────────────────────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/test-admin
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### ─── 8. Protected Route — No Token (should fail 401) ─────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/test-protected


### ─── 9. Refresh Token (via body) ─────────────────────────────
# In production the cookie is sent automatically. For testing,
# copy the refreshToken from login response:
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refreshToken": "PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}


### ─── 10. Forgot Password ────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "john@acme.com"
}


### ─── 11. Forgot Password — Non-existent email ──────────────
# Should return same success message (no email enumeration)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "ghost@nowhere.com"
}


### ─── 12. Reset Password ────────────────────────────────────
# Copy the token from server console log output
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "token": "PASTE_RESET_TOKEN_FROM_CONSOLE",
  "newPassword": "NewSecurePass456"
}


### ─── 13. Login with new password ────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "john@acme.com",
  "password": "NewSecurePass456"
}


### ─── 14. Logout ──────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refreshToken": "PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}


### ─── 15. 404 — Unknown route ─────────────────────────────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/nonexistent
